  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "According to Floridi (2023), AI systems merely act without embodying intelligence, making it nonsensical to discuss or measure intelligence in their context.",
    "This perspective is grounded in the belief that an intelligent outcome does not necessarily stem from intelligent behavior.",
    "While this may hold some truth, it's a rather extreme stance.",
    "It dismisses the possibility of recognizing certain tools as intelligent, which, by conventional standards, are considered intelligent and perform tasks deemed intelligent by humans.",
    "This viewpoint, however, overlooks the significance of the knowledge AI can generate and its impact on human epistemic and communicative practices."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "According to Floridi (2023), AI systems merely act without embodying intelligence, making it nonsensical to discuss or measure intelligence in their context."
  ]
}